es women. Most especially women. When it comes to preventing conflict or building peace, there's a way in which women ARE the experts. Think of how intimately women know their homes. If the lights are out, we can walk through rooms without bumping into anything. If a stranger has been there, we sense it. That's how well we know our communities. We know who belongs, and who is a potentially threatening stranger. We know the history. We know the people. We knew how to talk to an ex-combatant and get his cooperation, because we know where he comes from. To outsiders like the UN, these soldiers were a problem to be managed. But they were our children.\"","rating":4,"shelving":{"__typename":"Shelving","shelf":{"__typename":"Shelf","name":"read","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/627603?shelf=read"},"taggings":[],"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/235720608"},"likeCount":3,"viewerHasLiked":null,"commentCount":0,"viewerCanComment({\"resourceType\":\"review\"})":null},"User:7897834":{"id":7897834,"__typename":"User","legacyId":7897834,"imageUrlSquare":"https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1568220558i/7897834._UX200_CR0,33,200,200_.jpg","isAuthor":false,"textReviewsCount":1494,"viewableName":"Dimitris Papastergiou","isBlockedByViewer":false,"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/user/show/7897834-dimitris-papastergiou","contributor":null,"isFollowing":false,"isFriend":false,"followersCount":44},"Review:kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.CCYN4SSuU7vHvNLpmJAZ4w":{"id":"kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.CCYN4SSuU7vHvNLpmJAZ4w","__typename":"Review","book":{"__ref":"Book:kca://book/amzn1.gr.book.v1.vLf8RHSmt0yUSLQmlTZ04A"},"creator":{"__ref":"User:7897834"},"recommendFor":null,"updatedAt":1513332226699,"createdAt":1513263770000,"spoilerStatus":false,"lastRevisionAt":1513264527000,"text":"It was a good read. And a much more informative to the facts of the Liberian war than I expected.\u003c